<br>
Arch Shielding: level 44 HP/AC/Magic resist buff<br>
Diamondskin: level 44 &quot;rune&quot; spell<br>
Okeil's Flickering Flame: level 34 short-duration, 5-point damage shield with +10 fire resist.<br>
<br>
Smolder: not a wizard spell.  Does max 84 points of damage at 65.<br>
Enticement of Flame: level 44 fire-based &quot;mini-lure.&quot; (max  360 for 240 mana with 6 sec. casting time)<br>
Ice Shock: level 34 ice-based DD (max 318) <br>
Force Shock: level 20 &quot;all-or-nothing&quot; DD.  High resists. (max 179 with interrupt stun)<br>
<br>
<br>
All in all, I'm not impressed with that lineup of spells.  It doesn't jeopardize my job at all.  And if the mana pool is low, like suggested above, it's even worse, as many of these spells have horrendous ratios and long casting times.<br>
<br>
